Block of Code: set of instructions.
It will execute only when that specific condition is true.
Condition: An expression that evaluates the result(true or false)
Console.log(5>4)
Methods:
If :only one possible condition.
If the condition is true it will execute other wise it will skip.
Syntax:
If(condition){//Block of code}
Else if
Else
Switch
Ternary Operator

Practical Implementation:
